#Resolve hour differences between Linux and Windows in case of dualboot (Type the following command in Linux terminal)

timedatectl set-local-rtc 1 --adjust-system-clock

#Sometimes doesn't work so you can "roolback" using : 

timedatectl set-local-rtc 0 --adjust-system-clock

#Working everytime (Debian) : 

vi /etc/default/rcS
[...]
UTC=no
[...]

#Working everytime (Arch) :
vi /etc/adjtime
[...]
LOCAL #instead of "UTC"
[...]

Reboot
